story:
Whereas it is hereby recited for the record, and further to the tenor of memory and oath, that in the season when the river mists lay low and the imperial banners were yet undecided, a deputation embarked upon waters and routes of uncertain temperament, and whereas the attendant who is the subject hereof did bear responsibilities of tending, dressing, and comforting those afflicted by cut, fever, and fright, hereinafter the attendant shall be referred to as "the Healer", and whereas such denomination is adopted for the purposes of narrative clarity and shall not be construed as exhaustive of duty;

Whereas the Healer, being versed in compress, poultice, and pulse, did travel in a craft provisioned with jars of vinegar and ashes, with withered roots catalogued by scent and weight, and whereas the Healer's hands, callused at the fingertips and deft at the knot, performed sutures by lamplight and administered broths after midnight, the following recital attests to the actions taken when night and tide conspired against comfort;

Whereas the crossing was beset by shoal and gust, by sudden blackness and the cry of gulls, and whereas the hull shuddered under load and the sky poured itself as if to rewrite the manifest, the Healer stood upon decks that pitched like a sleeping beast and wrapped torn linen upon shoulders that bore both storm and scorn; and whereas the Healer spoke with a voice measured to soothe and to command, such voice issued orders about warmth, about elevation of limb, about the placement of heat-packs and the reconstitution of powdered herbs;

Whereas among effects kept close to the Healer's person was an object commonly used for guidance in the selection of victuals, which, by fate and fray, became repository and record; a stained paper menu, folded and annotated, survived the waves and served as a ledger of tastes. The menu, hereinafter "the Menu", was written with the same ink that smudged the margins of medical notes and was used, in emergency, as a splint, as a bandage, and as witness that life may persist through small pleasures;

Whereas also carried upon the person of the Healer was a single floral emblem, affixed by thread to a waist-knot, which was preserved against salt and wind as talisman and as memento, and whereas that emblem retained fragrance despite damp and despite the rubbing of sails, a single daffodil, pressed against the healer's heart, smelled of spring and duty. That daffodil, hereinafter "the Daffodil", served alternately as promise to a distant kin and as cipher of home upon which the Healer's hands returned in moments when the crew feared loss;

Whereas the narrative shall further state that, in consequence of tempest and remedy, the Healer effected rescues of limb and hope, administering clot and calamus, and whereas those whom the Healer tended later gave testimony under the breath of stars that the Healer's calm guided them from delirium to rest, it follows that the record of this crossing is to be preserved in speech and in folded paper;

Whereas this account, being thus composed of clauses and recollection, is intended to stand as formal remembrance, and whereas those who read shall find in the particulars of bandage, menu, and flower the architecture of courage that binds practitioner to patient and voyage to home, the recital concludes with the attestation that the Healer, having acted within measure and beyond fear, remained the principal steward of care aboard the vessel.
